UPDATE lessons SET content = '<div class="no-overflow"><p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"><strong>Summary</strong></p><p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"></p><ul><li><strong>Strive for moderation</strong><strong>.&nbsp;</strong>You know that saying “<em>too much of a good thing</em>”? That’s often the case with coping. Coping strategies can cross from being healthy to unhealthy when you do too much (or get too much) of something. For example, we need food to survive and stay healthy. But when food becomes a source of comfort, and we overeat, food then moves into the unhealthy zone. So, strive for moderation. If food, sleep, work, or something else becomes a crutch, you need to reevaluate its role in your life.</li></ul><p></p><ul><li><strong>Choose a regular time to meditate.&nbsp;</strong>It’s easier to make meditation a habit if you meditate at the same time every day. For example, you might decide to meditate first thing in the morning, over lunch, or as a way to decompress immediately after returning home from work. Choose a time that’s most beneficial or convenient for you.</li></ul><p></p><ul><li><strong>Switch it up.&nbsp;</strong>Try switching up your exercise routines to make it more interesting and exciting. If you usually go for a walk, try going for a bike ride instead. Or, join a new dance class or an ultimate Frisbee team. Try something new to keep exercise fresh and stimulating!</li></ul><p></p><ul><li><strong>Get outside perspective.&nbsp;</strong>Sometimes it’s challenging to evaluate our thoughts fairly and objectively because we’re so close to them. If you’re stuck, then seek outside perspective. You might get the input of your spouse, family member, or a close mentor or friend. Or, consider enlisting the help of a professional therapist. &nbsp;</li></ul><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><ul><li><strong>There are no rules.</strong>&nbsp;As you follow the tips covered in this lesson, keep in mind that the most important journaling rule is that there are no rules. Ultimately, your journal is about you. So, while this lesson is a helpful starting point, don’t hesitate to get creative, do what feels comfortable, and think outside the box.</li></ul><p></p><ul><li><strong>Find something to laugh about.&nbsp;</strong>Not only can laughter lighten your mood, but it also lowers cortisol and releases feel-good endorphins. So, consider attending a comedy show, turning on a funny television series or movie, or calling up a friend who always knows how to make you laugh.</li></ul><p></p><ul><li><strong>Fake it until you make it.</strong>&nbsp;If you aren’t 100% convinced that your actions largely determine the circumstances in your life, keep telling yourself you have control over your life. Act like you have the power until you’ve internalized it.</li></ul><p></p><p></p><p><ul><li><strong>The 5-4-3-2-1 technique.</strong>&nbsp;If you have less than five minutes to spare, the 5-4-3-2-1 technique is a quicker variation of our grounding exercise. This technique engages your five senses, just as in the process we explored. But you don’t need to give a full minute to each sense. Here’s how it works: Look at&nbsp;<em>five</em>&nbsp;things, touch&nbsp;<em>four</em>&nbsp;things, listen to&nbsp;<em>three</em>&nbsp;things, smell&nbsp;<em>two</em>&nbsp;things, and taste&nbsp;<em>one</em>&nbsp;thing. Though brief, this exercise can still distract you from your thoughts and center you on the present moment.</li></ul></p><p></p><p></p></div>' WHERE slug = 'module-3-strategies-to-relieve-stress-module-summary';
UPDATE lessons SET content = '<div class="no-overflow"><p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"></p><p dir="ltr"><strong>After completing this module, you will be able to:<br></strong><br></p><ul><li><strong>Understand </strong>cybersecurity</li><li><strong>Implement </strong>best practices for secure internet browsing</li><li><strong>Implement</strong>&nbsp;best practices for public WI-FI security</li><li><strong>Know-how </strong>to use social media safely</li><li><strong>Know-how </strong>to deal with security incident</li></ul><br><br><p></p></div>' WHERE slug = 'module-1-online-security-fundamentals-learning-outcome';
