UPDATE lessons SET content = '<div class="no-overflow"><p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"><strong>Summary</strong></p><p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"></p><ul><li>Sometimes we discover that a job just isn’t the right fit—maybe the culture isn’t what you expected, or the compensation doesn’t support your personal goals. In this case, it may be time to consider a career switch.</li></ul><p></p><ul><li><strong>Purpose is a moving target.</strong>&nbsp;It changes over time as your values and circumstances change. Check in with yourself regularly to stay connected to what matters most—and give yourself permission to let your purpose evolve.</li></ul><p></p><ul><li><strong>Try something new.&nbsp;</strong>You might be the life of the party or the first to leave. Or you might love hearing stories but feel it’s too risky to share about yourself. Maybe you’ve never had a conversation with Gary from accounting. Whatever your habits, shake them up and see what surprises unfold.&nbsp;</li></ul><p></p><ul><li><strong>The best habits are the ones that work for you.</strong>&nbsp;Not every habit will be right for you, and that’s OK. If a habit doesn’t resonate with you, is hard to stick to, or doesn’t have a positive impact, ditch it and move on to one that does.</li></ul><p></p><ul><li><strong>You can practice flow with almost every activity.&nbsp;</strong>For example, you can experience it while organizing spreadsheets, cooking dinner, and journaling before bed. Keep an eye out for opportunities to add flow to your life.</li></ul><p></p><ul><li><strong>Emotions are fleeting.</strong>&nbsp;Sometimes, you have to weather a storm of negative emotions. But positive emotions can be just as temporary. When you learn how not to get too attached to your emotions—whether good or bad—it creates a healthier perspective.</li></ul><p><ul><li><strong>Managers, reframe success for perfectionist team members.&nbsp;</strong>Set an expectation that mistakes are normal and show tolerance and patience. Help them focus on connecting to a journey with purpose and self-care rather than that elusive carrot.</li></ul></p><p><br></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div>' WHERE slug = 'module-3-positive-psychology-in-the-workplace-module-summary';
UPDATE lessons SET content = '<div class="no-overflow"><p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"><strong>After completing this module, you will be able to:</strong></p><p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"></p><ul><li><span><strong>Understand</strong> the difference between Diversity, Inclusion and Belonging (DIBS).</span></li><li>Have the <strong>capability</strong> to implement Diversity, Inclusion and Belonging in the Workplace.</li><li><strong>Know-how</strong> to attract and hire diverse talent that can lead to higher company performance.</li><li><strong>Know-how</strong> to retain diverse talent.</li><li><strong>Implement</strong> tools that will quantify and measure Diversity, Inclusion and Belonging.</li><li>Make <strong>strategic decisions</strong> that will make your company to be an Ally of Diversity, Inclusion and Belonging.</li></ul><p></p></div>' WHERE slug = 'module-2-diversity-inclusion-and-belonging-learning-outcome';
