UPDATE lessons SET content = '<div class="no-overflow"><p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"><strong>Summary</strong></p><p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"></p><ul><li>Get to know your people. The role of an HR professional starts with people. Get to know your employees’ skill sets, strengths, goals, backgrounds, challenges, and preferences. Create personal connections with staff and learn about their interests and what they care about. The more in tune you are with your company’s staff, the more likely you are to understand and support their needs.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</li><li>Involve other employees in the process. Consider involving soon-to-be coworkers in the resume screening and interview process. For example, you might add a final interview between top candidates and those who will be working closest with the chosen candidate. That approach gives both sides a chance to get to know who they might be working with and develop a better sense of the workplace culture fit.<br></li></ul><ul><li>Keep your reviews consistent. When reviewing resumes/CV, it’s tempting to get distracted by extra details, such as if you went to the same school as an applicant or have a similar hobby. But that information can prevent you from remaining objective. So, keep your reviews consistent by following the same three step process for every applicant—remembering that the same rules should apply to everyone.</li></ul><ul><li>Don’t base compensation on employees’ previous salaries from their previous jobs or companies. Not only can this practice lead to unfair compensation, but it also doesn’t reflect the specific job value, individual value, or internal equity of your company and the employee’s new position.</li></ul><ul><li>Tell your team about a new hire before that person arrives. It’s not a good experience for a new hire to arrive on their first day, only to find out that no one knows who they are or why they’re there. Keep your team in the loop and give them context about who a new hire is, what their title will be, when they will start, and what they’ll be doing—before they get there.</li></ul><ul><li>Schedule regular reviews. Schedule time to review employment laws and audit your HR practices regularly. Check key government websites such as the U.S. Department of Labor’s site. Audit HR practices with labor law compliance in mind, including employee compensation and benefits, hiring and firing practices, training, job assignments and promotions, employee conduct guidelines, and general workplace conditions.</li></ul><p></p></div>' WHERE slug = 'module-1-hr-fundamentals-module-summary';
UPDATE lessons SET content = '<div class="no-overflow"><p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"></p><p dir="ltr"><strong>After completing this module, you will be able to:</strong></p><p dir="ltr"></p><ul><li><strong>Prepare, plan and execute </strong>a successful job interview.</li><li><strong>Understand </strong>which job interview type to implement.</li><li><strong>Know-how</strong>&nbsp;to conduct an effective job interview.</li><li><strong>Know-how</strong>&nbsp;to craft strong interview questions.</li><li><strong>Implement</strong>&nbsp;a non-bias interview.</li><li><strong>Implement </strong>a process to follow up after an interview.</li></ul><br><p></p></div>' WHERE slug = 'module-3-interviewing-learning-outcome';
