UPDATE lessons SET content = '<div class="no-overflow"><p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<video controls="true"><source src="https://goalvow.com/upskilling/pluginfile.php/629/mod_label/intro/5_HR_Talent%20Management.mp4">https://goalvow.com/upskilling/pluginfile.php/629/mod_label/intro/5_HR_Talent%20Management.mp4</video>&nbsp;<br></p></div>' WHERE slug = 'module-5-talent-management-lesson-5-strategies-for-retaining-talent-and-minimizing-turnover';
UPDATE lessons SET content = '<div class="no-overflow"><p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"><strong>Summary</strong></p><p dir="ltr"></p><ul><li>Don’t ignore the process. To achieve ongoing sustainability and improve long-term performance, you must follow every step of the talent management process. Remember each of the four steps and don’t ignore the process. If you do, it could cause a dangerous gap and leave your company vulnerable to the competition.</li></ul><p></p><ul><li>Your strategy is uniquely your own. When creating an effective talent management strategy, remember that your exact approach and goals should be uniquely your own. As you follow along with these steps, try not to rely on cookie-cutter employees or policies. Get creative. Focus on your specific company needs. And find ways to stand out.</li></ul><p></p><ul><li>Don’t settle for the wrong candidate. It’s easy to get frustrated and settle for the wrong candidate. But if you’re receiving an overflow of under-qualified applicants, there may be a larger issue. Rather than settling, rethink your hiring strategy. What are you doing wrong, and what could you do better? Build an organization where your ideal candidates want to work, and you’ll improve your long-term business success.</li></ul><p></p><ul><li>A culture of development. For an in-house talent development program to work, you must create a culture that fosters continuous growth. From day one, educate employees on your company’s commitment to developing talent. Then, continue to reinforce this message with regular one-on-one meetings and feedback. Development must be more than just an optimistic idea, but a tangible reality that every employee strives toward.</li></ul><p><ul><li>Listen to your team. Every workplace is unique. If you hope to retain your employees, you must understand what would make them stay. Talk with them to discover what they want most. Then, offer as many of those perks and benefits as you can. And when employees do depart your organization, conduct exit interviews to find out why. That insight can help you better understand how to keep your other team members on board for the long term.</li></ul></p></div>' WHERE slug = 'module-5-talent-management-module-summary';
UPDATE lessons SET content = '<div class="no-overflow"><p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"></p><p dir="ltr"><strong>After completing this module, you will be able to:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Know-the </strong>unconscious bias and what impact it does.</li><li><strong>Understand</strong>&nbsp;different types of unconscious bias.</li><li><strong>Capable</strong>&nbsp;of implementing strategies to help others overcome unconscious bias.<br></li><li><strong>Implement</strong>&nbsp;processes to help avoid bias while recruiting and retaining talent.</li></ul><br><p></p></div>' WHERE slug = 'module-4-unconscious-bias-learning-outcome';
