UPDATE lessons SET content = '<div class="no-overflow"><p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"><strong>Summary</strong></p><p dir="ltr"></p><ul><li><strong>Never buy email lists.</strong> Purchasing an email list and sending unsolicited messages may seem like an easy way to fast-track building your subscriber list, but it can harm your brand in the long run. Sending messages only to those individuals who opt in and are eager to hear from you will garner better results. Remember, a smaller list of high-quality leads is better than an extensive list of uninterested (and likely annoyed) recipients.</li></ul><p></p><ul><li><strong>Cherish your email lists and work to grow them.</strong> Other communication platforms like social media are largely out of your control. Your subscribers and followers could be banned or deleted, or the entire platform could go away. But your email list will always belong to you.</li></ul><p></p><ul><li><strong>Set a calendar reminder now to review spam filter rules.</strong> Since rules change frequently, a reminder will keep frequent rule checks from slipping your mind—and keep you ahead of gatekeepers.</li></ul><p></p><ul><li><strong>Test your subject lines.</strong> Predicting which technique will work for a given situation isn’t always easy. That’s why testing is so important. Don’t leave it to chance—instead, be methodical. A/B testing allows you to compare two subject lines to find out which is more effective. Simply create two different subject lines (Version A and Version B) for the same email, send them to your recipients, and examine the results to gauge which one performs better.</li></ul><p></p><ul><li><strong>Have fun and explore—the possibilities are endless. </strong>There are so many ways to get creative with audience segmentation. Brainstorm ideas and play around to find your pot of gold.</li></ul><p></p><ul><li><strong>Always keep your readers in mind.</strong> What do they expect from your organization? How does your email benefit them? Your audience will respond positively to emails that they feel are relevant. Consider their expectations as you create email campaigns.</li></ul><p></p><ul><li><strong>Keep testing.</strong> Don’t run an A/B test once and stop. Customer preferences and attitudes continually&nbsp; evolve. Keep experimenting and conducting A/B tests to stay ahead of changing market trends.</li></ul><p></p><ul><li><strong>Less is more.</strong> Take a minimalist approach and ask yourself: Is anything distracting? It’s rare for people to read an entire email, so make it easy for them to skim by including the bare essentials with a few eye catching details.</li></ul><p></p><ul><li><strong>Don’t be annoying.</strong> Emails are so easy to send that it can be tempting to send one too many. Pay attention to the timing and frequency of your automated emails to avoid alienating your customer base.</li></ul><p><ul><li><strong>Improve your email list quality with better sign-up practices.</strong> On your website, place the sign-up button where it’s easy to find, like at the top of the page. Ask users to double-opt-in—not just provide an email but verify their sign-up and contact details. That will help improve deliverability and engagement, which, in turn, will improve your results!</li></ul></p></div>' WHERE slug = 'module-9-email-marketing-module-summary';
UPDATE lessons SET content = '<div class="no-overflow"><h4 dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"><strong>Learning Outcome</strong></h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>After completing this module, you will be able to:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Understand </strong>the fundamentals of marketing</li>\r\n<li><strong>Know </strong>the difference and value between traditional marketing and digital marketing</li>\r\n<li><strong>Know-how </strong>to apply the key elements of marketing</li>\r\n<li><strong>Know-how </strong>to develop a marketing plan</li>\r\n<li>Be <strong>capable </strong>of refining and understand your Unique Selling Point (USP)</li>\r\n<li><strong>Understand </strong>the<strong> </strong>customer buying stages and how to stimulate them to create retention. </li>\r\n<li>Be <strong>capable </strong>of creating a <strong>Go-To-Market strategy</strong> that works from your marketing analytics</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><br><br></p>\r\n<p></p></div>' WHERE slug = 'module-1-marketing-fundamentals-learning-outcome';
