UPDATE lessons SET content = '<div class="no-overflow"><p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"><strong>Summary</strong></p><p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"></p><ul><li>Even if your company doesn’t have a dedicated product marketing department, it’s essential to\r\nunderstand and carry out the typical functions of product marketers. Knowing what your customers\r\nvalue and how to meet their needs with your offerings will set each product up for success in the\r\nmarketplace.<br></li></ul><p></p><ul><li>Lean on the sales team. They’re on the front lines and hear from customers daily. They know what\r\ncustomers think. Ask, “What makes customers excited about this product?” and “What do they wish we did\r\nbetter?” Use these insights to get a more straightforward path.<br></li></ul><p></p><ul><li>Think ahead. Global brands stay in this phase for decades by predicting what’s next and preparing.\r\nAlways keep one eye on the market. What trends or services might render you obsolete? Strengthen your\r\nposition or move to a new one.</li></ul><p></p><ul><li>Use time and resources to your advantage. Especially while you’re still profitable, take time to plan your\r\nnext move. Meet customer needs as you grow. Pay attention to what matters most to them, and adapt whenever you\r\ncan.</li></ul><p></p><ul><li>Don’t be afraid to pivot. If you’re having difficulty achieving product-market fit, you may need to\r\nreconsider the offering. Examine the market closely to understand what people want and aren’t getting\r\nelsewhere. Then, tailor your idea to meet those needs. Many successful companies started with one\r\nconcept and changed course when they recognized an underserved opportunity in the market.</li></ul><p></p><ul><li>Experiment with pricing. When it comes to pricing, there is no one-size-fits-all approach. Experiment\r\nwith different strategies, markets, and price points to figure out what works best for you. Prices should&nbsp;never be set in stone. Be prepared to make changes based on a variety of factors in order to stay\r\nprofitable.</li></ul><p></p><ul><li>Releasing a new product or entering a new market is inherently risky. A solid go-to-market strategy can\r\nhelp you mitigate some risks by predicting potential opportunities and threats—while staying flexible\r\nenough to change course when needed.</li></ul><p></p><ul><li>Study your favorite products. Many famous brands are known for their launch events, pre-launch\r\nmarketing, and buzz-building. What are some favorite elements that excited you about these products?\r\nCan you emulate any of their strategies?</li></ul><p></p><p></p><p></p><ul><li>Your product page should reflect your branding. Customers may click directly on your product page\r\nfrom an ad or search result—which means they may not ever see your homepage before buying. Make\r\nsure each product page showcases your brand’s personality, voice, and style.</li></ul><p></p><ul><li>Don’t lie or exaggerate. Writing compelling marketing copy does not mean exaggerating product\r\nbenefits or making false claims. Always check your product descriptions for accuracy before publishing.</li></ul><p></p><ul><li>Think about different marketing strategies that might appeal to each adopter category. While targeting\r\nthe early adopters will be the most effective at generating widespread interest, try a creative exercise by\r\ncoming up with ideas to hook the other categories. What’s a point of entry that might entice even late\r\nmajority or laggard types?</li></ul><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div>' WHERE slug = 'module-3-product-marketing-module-summary';
UPDATE lessons SET content = '<div class="no-overflow"><p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"></p><p dir="ltr"><strong>After completing this module, you will be able to:</strong></p><p dir="ltr"></p><ul><li><strong>Understand </strong>the basics of Search Engine Optimization (SEO)</li><li>Have the&nbsp;<strong>capability</strong>&nbsp;to select keywords that will improve your SEO</li><li><strong>Know-how&nbsp;</strong>to optimize your website content to improve your SEO ranking</li><li><strong>Implement </strong>link building strategies for SEO</li><li><strong>Know-how</strong>&nbsp;to structure your website for SEO</li><li><strong>Know-how </strong>to improve your image optimization for SEO</li></ul><br><br><p></p></div>' WHERE slug = 'module-7-search-engine-optimization-learning-outcome';
