UPDATE lessons SET content = '<div class="no-overflow"><p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<video controls="true"><source src="https://goalvow.com/upskilling/pluginfile.php/696/mod_label/intro/9_Search%20Engine%20Marketing%20%28SEO%29.mp4">https://goalvow.com/upskilling/pluginfile.php/696/mod_label/intro/9_Search%20Engine%20Marketing%20%28SEO%29.mp4</video>&nbsp;<br></p></div>' WHERE slug = 'module-7-search-engine-optimization-lesson-9-six-must-know-image-optimization-tips';
UPDATE lessons SET content = '<div class="no-overflow"><p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"><strong>Summary</strong></p><p dir="ltr"></p><ul><li><strong>SEO software can help. </strong>Ranking in organic search results doesn’t cost money, but it can pay dividends. Don’t have an in-house SEO guru? No problem. Software platforms can assist with critical tasks like keyword research and link building. Just make sure the platform you select has a good reputation for quality work.</li></ul><p></p><ul><li><strong>Don’t forget localized keywords.</strong> Many businesses only operate in certain geographical areas. You can incorporate local keywords like ZIP codes, city or state names, or even neighborhood names to tailor keywords to local consumers.</li></ul><p></p><ul><li><strong>A warning about “black hat” SEO.</strong> Black hat SEO is the term for aggressive and ethically questionable SEO practices like keyword stuffing, hiding text, and purchasing backlinks. These practices might get your domain blocked or classified as spam by major search engines.</li></ul><p></p><ul><li><strong>T</strong><strong>echnical SEO is a long game.</strong> No one masters all aspects overnight. Instead, set a schedule to tackle a problem or two at a time. Then, conduct a regular SEO audit to update the XML site map, fix links, and address indexing problems.</li></ul><p></p><ul><li><strong>Optimize internal links, too.</strong> External links may get all the attention, but internal links are important, too. Internal links connect one page of your website to another. Internally linking to your most important pages helps search engines understand and rank your site better.</li></ul><p></p><ul><li><strong>Get a good planning bonus. </strong>You’ve made a clear plan for the site and URLs, so you have everything you need to submit an XML site map to Google Search Console and Bing Webmaster Tools. A site map is simply a listing of your pages, giving search engines one more clue to crawl and index your pages the way you intend.</li></ul><p></p><ul><li><strong>Think of your reader. </strong>A lot goes into creating well-crafted alt text. But the most important thing to keep in mind is that you’re writing descriptions for people who can’t see your images. So, think of your reader. What do they need to know? And how can you communicate that information succinctly?</li></ul><p></p><ul><li><strong>Continue exploring image optimization.</strong> Image optimization is a complex, detailed topic—and covering everything in a single lesson would be impossible. Take what you’ve learned in this lesson to get started with image optimization, but don’t stop your journey. There’s still much to explore to give your page that extra edge. Continue learning, and you’ll reap the rewards of a high-performing website that delights users and lures in search engines.</li></ul><p></p></div>' WHERE slug = 'module-7-search-engine-optimization-module-summary';
UPDATE lessons SET content = '<div class="no-overflow"><p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"></p><p dir="ltr"><strong>After completing this module, you will be able to:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Implement </strong>your social media strategy</li><li>Have the&nbsp;<strong>capability</strong>&nbsp;to choose the right social media channels based on your value offering</li><li><strong>Know-how </strong>to use content buckets for social media organization and planning</li><li><strong>Understand</strong>&nbsp;the best social media practices for businesses&nbsp;</li><li><strong>Get </strong><strong>started</strong> with social listening</li><li><strong>Know-how </strong>to use hashtags for social media marketing</li><li><strong>Boost </strong>your social media engagement</li><li><strong>Capable </strong>of monitoring your social media metrics</li></ul><br><br><p></p></div>' WHERE slug = 'module-8-social-media-marketing-learning-outcome';
